  "transcriptSegment": "Basecamp implemented this system company-wide after their C T O noticed their junior developers couldn't debug simple issues without assistance. They started with mandatory ten-minute thinking periods before any A I use. Within three months, their bug resolution time actually improved, and developers reported feeling more confident tackling new challenges.\n\nThe key is that you're not fighting willpower against addiction. You're redirecting the same reward system that got you hooked in the first place. Your brain starts finding satisfaction in the thinking process again instead of just the instant gratification of getting answers.",
